HSBC WORLD MATCH PLAY CHAMPIONSHIP
October 14, 2007
Angel Cabrera
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   


   ANGEL CABRERA:  Thanks very much. I've had a great week and played well all week. I played my best today but it wasn't enough, because Ernie played very well. He is the King of Wentworth. He lives here, he knows the course and it is his own back-yard, so he is very comfortable and happy here.   
 2007 has been a great year for me. This week has been great, and of course, winning the US Open has changed my life. I wasn't happy with my form this year until then, but I got lucky and won there, and it's been a great year since then.   
 I congratulate Ernie - he is a great champion - but I hope that the Pumas win tonight in Paris and will have better luck than I did.   
   
